				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I have a CRT HDTV that looks okay with NES, but still doesn't work properly. The main problem with it is with any game that scrolls - the frame will jump every few seconds or so. <br />I believe this is due to the NES running at almost 60.1 frames/sec and the TV being locked to 59.9 frames/sec and the hardware periodically re-syncing to the NES signal. Until a hardware manufacturer properly addresses these issues hold onto your old CRTs tight.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

